cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for learning transferable adversarial examples using neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the paper deals with image classification tasks. The paper also involves adversarial attacks, which can be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses longitudinal ensemble, which is a technique used in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
